FBIS4-55491 "dreeu095_i_94011" FBIS-EEU-94-095 Daily Report 17 May 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Patriarchs To Meet Karadzic Patriarchs To Meet Karadzic AU1705091894 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in Serbo-Croatian 0800 GMT 17 May 94 AU1705091894 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Text] Patriarch Aleksiy of Moscow and all of Russia and Serbian Patriarch Pavle are going to visit the republic of Srpska, where they will visit the seat of the Davro-Bosnian metropolitan in Sokolac and talk to Metropolitan Nikolaj. The ecclesiastical dignitaries will hold talks in Pale with the leadership of the republic of Srpska, including President Radovan Karadzic. A visit with Russian members of the UN Protection Force in the Sarajevo Serbian settlement of Grbavica is scheduled to take place afterwards. The Russian and Serbian patriarchs are supposed to meet with Zagreb Cardinal Franjo Kuharic and Reis-ul-Ulema Mustafa Ceric at Sarajevo airport. It is planned that Patriarchs Aleksiy II and Pavle, together with Russian and Serbian bishops, will bless the land on which the Serbian Orthodox Church will be built.
